        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1680",
        "content": "Margaret and Dixon had been at work for two days, unpacking and arranging, but everything inside the house still looked in disorder; and outside a thick fog crept up to the very windows, and was driven in to every open door in choking white wreaths of unwholesome mist.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
